PERIPHERAL DEVICE INTERFACES:

Peripheral interfaces allow external devices (like keyboards, printers, external drives) to connect to a computer system — either wired or wirelessly.
For example:
• Peripheral device
- USB
- FireWire
- Thunderbolt
- Bluetooth
- RF

